If you are willing to consider non-GR theories of gravity, then here
is an example of such an experiment. Shoot bullets inside your boxcar
and measure how their accelerations depend on the magnitudes and
directions of their velocities. These dependencies will be different
for the two situations (with and without the gravitational field).
This is explained in section 5.1 of http://www.arxiv.org/abs/physics/0612019

