This should work: set up a sensitive pivoted rod parallel to the axis
of rotation, with pivot along the orbit,  with masses m at each end.
Given a little start or offset angle A, a tidal acceleration
omega^2*L*sinA will cause the rod to align radially. The forces are
omega^2*(R - .5LsinA)  and omega^2*(R + .5Lsin A).
John Polasek
